## Note Nodes

```
id:               note_pg16_perf
name:             PG16 performance gains are real
tag: research
phase: forged
confidence: solid
source: Benchmarks on staging (2026-03-28)
weight: heavy
notes:            Query planner improvements gave 12-18% speedup on our heaviest analytic queries; COPY is 2x faster with new binary format
```

```
id:               note_timescale_risk
name:             TimescaleDB may not support PG16 in time
tag: infrastructure
phase: refining
confidence: provisional
weight: heavy
notes:            Community edition lagging behind; enterprise fork has a beta but no GA date. Fallback: native partitioning + pg_cron
```

```
id:               note_api_consumers
name:             Only three external consumers use v1
tag: design
phase: forged
confidence: solid
source: API gateway logs, March 2026
weight: medium
notes:            PartnerA (80% of traffic), PartnerB (15%), PartnerC (5%). All on annual contracts renewing Q3.
```

```
id:               note_nagios_debt
name:             Nagios config is 4000 lines of undocumented checks
tag: operations
phase: forged
confidence: solid
source: SRE audit, February 2026
weight: medium
notes:            60% of checks are for decommissioned services. No one knows who wrote the rest. Rewriting from scratch is faster than untangling.
```

```
id:               note_vendor_pricing
name:             Vendor B pricing model penalises burst traffic
tag: research
phase: refining
confidence: provisional
weight: medium
notes:            Per-node-hour billing with no burst credits. Our Black Friday traffic pattern would cost 3x normal month. Vendor A has committed-use discounts.
```

```
id:               note_launch_timing
name:             Marketing wants launch tied to conference
tag: communication
phase: raw
confidence: speculative
weight: light
notes:            KubeCon EU in mid-April suggested as launch moment. Tight but possible if migration completes on schedule.
```

